                            <comment id="404729" author="simmonsja" created="Thu, 22 Feb 2024 01:17:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch lays down the foundation to support really large data sets in the user land library. After this lands you can change the cb-&amp;gt;min_dump_alloc field for your Netlink kernel code to allocate the needed skbuf size to send the message back. Note SLES12SP5 only supports up to only 64K size. I think we can work around this by using pskb_expand_head(). I will have to investigate for this case.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
